This paper is about simultaneous machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a new attention mechanism for neural machine translation (NMT), which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), hence it could also be categorized under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper uses NMT to translate speech, which involves processing audio signals, and could therefore be categorized under "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper could also be categorized under "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) as it deals with processing visual and audio signals.
